<h2 style=3D"font-weight: bold; font-family: &quot;Arial Black&quot;, Arial=
, Helvetica, sans-serif; letter-spacing: -1px; font-size: 20px; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; margin: 0px; padding: 16px 0px =
5px;">SEC: Whistleblowers</h2>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Here is <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloomberg=
business.com/click/32912729.260424/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9uZXdzL3ByZXNz=
LXJlbGVhc2UvMjAyMy0yMTM/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB65c1774c" itemprop=3D"Stor=
yLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; t=
ext-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-co=
lor: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> one aga=
inst D.E. Shaw &amp; Co.</a>, the big hedge fund, for violating whistleblow=
er laws. For a long time, hedge funds (and many other employers) have asked=
 employees to sign nondisclosure=C2=A0agreements that traditionally say=C2=
=A0something like=C2=A0=E2=80=9Cyou agree not to disclose any confidential =
information unless you are required to by law or a court order.=E2=80=9D So=
metimes they also add =E2=80=9Cand, if you <em>are </em>required to disclos=
e it by law, you=E2=80=99ll tell us first.=E2=80=9D</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The SEC takes the position that this is illega=
l. If your hedge fund is doing fraud, and you learn about that in the cours=
e of your employment, then (1) the SEC would like you to come in and blow t=
he whistle on your employer but (2) your nondisclosure agreement says that =
you can=E2=80=99t: The fraud is confidential information of the fund, and y=
ou=E2=80=99re not allowed to disclose it unless=C2=A0<em>required </em>to b=
y=C2=A0law. In theory, if you went in to the SEC as a voluntary whistleblow=
er and said =E2=80=9Chere=E2=80=99s some bad stuff,=E2=80=9D the SEC might =
investigate and fine your firm, and then they might turn around and sue you=
 saying =E2=80=9Csure we were doing fraud but you weren=E2=80=99t=C2=A0<em>=
legally required=C2=A0</em>to disclose it, that was just a choice you made,=
 and it violated your NDA.=E2=80=9D <em>Obviously they would not do that,=
=C2=A0</em>because it would be a bad look but also because it is prohibited=
 by whistleblower protection laws. But the language of the NDA makes it pos=
sible, so arguably the NDA is itself illegal, a violation of whistleblower =
laws: The abstract theoretical <em>threat</em> of being sued for going to t=
he SEC is enough to deter whistleblowers.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The SEC has sued firms over this before, and i=
n 2017, after some of those cases,=C2=A0D.E. Shaw sent an email to its empl=
oyees being like =E2=80=9Cobviously we don=E2=80=99t mean that.=E2=80=9D (=
=E2=80=9CThe firm wishes to emphasize that you also have the ability to com=
municate directly with regulators and other governmental agencies regarding=
 possible violations of law or regulation without notice to the firm.=E2=80=
=9D) Still the employment agreements kept using the old language until 2019=
. Also, for a while, when people left D.E. Shaw, to get severance, they had=
 to sign a form saying that they had not filed any complaints about the fir=
m with =E2=80=9Cany regulatory authority,=E2=80=9D which also seems a littl=
e anti-whistleblower-y.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">D.E. Shaw paid $10 million. I hope somebody is=
 getting a whistleblower payment for this? Maybe the easiest lucrative job =
in finance is:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Take a job at a hedge fund.</li>=09<l=
i style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Get handed an employment agreement on the f=
irst day that says =E2=80=9Cyou agree not to disclose any of our secrets un=
less required by law.=E2=80=9D</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Sig=
n.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Take the agreement home with yo=
u.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Circle that sentence in red mar=
ker, write =E2=80=9C$$$$$!!!!!=E2=80=9D next to it and send it to the SEC.<=
/li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">The SEC extracts a $10 million fin=
e.=C2=A0</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">They <a href=3D"https://l=
ink.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/32912729.260424/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLm=
dvdi9uZXdzL3ByZXNzLXJlbGVhc2UvMjAyMy0xMzE/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB31bc314b=
" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D=
"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px=
; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-colo=
r: #ccc;"> give you $3 million</a>.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;=
">You can keep your job! Why not; it=E2=80=99s illegal to retaliate against=
 whistleblowers.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Or, you know, get=
 a new one and do it again.</li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Anyway there is no indication that D.E. Shaw d=
id anything else wrong, or that anyone was deterred from whistleblowing or =
whatever; this is just the price of writing the wrong sentence in the NDA.<=
/p>
