<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Lots of multinational businesses will employ l=
ocal third-party agents in foreign countries: To sell your product or win y=
our deal or get necessary licenses or whatever in some foreign country, you=
 might need to hire a local consultant with local knowledge and connections=
. And you=E2=80=99ll need to pay them somehow, a flat fee or an hourly rate=
 or a percentage of the deal size or whatever. And they will ideally use 10=
0% of that money to pay legitimate expenses and compensate themselves for t=
heir time, effort and expertise, and 0% of that money to pay bribes to loca=
l government officials. But it=E2=80=99s hard to be sure! It is your job to=
 be sure, though, under US anti-bribery laws.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">One pretty good tip-off that they=E2=80=99re p=
aying bribes is that if the local government official=C2=A0calls you up and=
 say =E2=80=9Chey, you should really pay your local agent a higher commissi=
on,=E2=80=9D that=E2=80=99s a bribe, man. Or if the local agent calls you u=
p and says =E2=80=9Chey, my friend the local government official really wan=
ts you to pay me a higher commission,=E2=80=9D bribe.<a class=3D"footnote-i=
ndex" href=3D"#footnote-2" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !=
important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-b=
ottom-style: none !important; background-color: transparent !important; dis=
play: inline-block;">
<span>[2]</span>
</a> Why would the local government official care how much your agent is ge=
tting paid? He cares because the money is going to him.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;"><a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness=
.com/click/32912729.260424/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9uZXdzL3ByZXNzLXJlbGVh=
c2UvMjAyMy0yMDk/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBcb3621a5" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" i=
temscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-deco=
ration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #00=
0000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">So</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The Securities and Exchange Commission [Friday=
]=C2=A0announced that Charlotte-based Albemarle Corporation, a global speci=
alty chemicals company, agreed to pay more than $103.6 million to settle th=
e SEC=E2=80=99s charges that it violated the anti-bribery, recordkeeping, a=
nd internal accounting controls provisions of the Foreign Corrupt Practices=
 Act (FCPA).</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">According to the SEC=E2=80=99s Order, despite =
significant red flags, Albemarle used agents from at least 2009 through 201=
7 that paid bribes to obtain sales of refinery catalysts to public-sector o=
il refineries in Vietnam, India, and Indonesia and to private-sector oil re=
fineries in India. In addition, the Order finds that Albemarle violated the=
 FCPA=E2=80=99s recordkeeping requirements and failed to devise and maintai=
n a sufficient system of internal accounting controls to provide reasonable=
 assurances that payments made to agents in Vietnam, Indonesia, India, Chin=
a, and the United Arab Emirates were for legitimate services.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The red flags are like:</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Beginning in 2013, Vietnam Agent m=
ade frequent requests to increase its commission. Emails from sales personn=
el in Asia and Europe reflected that Vietnam Agent had asserted that the co=
mmission increase was meant to =E2=80=9Csettle down,=E2=80=9D =E2=80=9Ctake=
 care [of],=E2=80=9D and =E2=80=9Ccontribute=E2=80=9D to state-owned refine=
ry officials. Increasing the commission, the sales personnel understood, wo=
uld be necessary to =E2=80=9Csecure orders,=E2=80=9D =E2=80=9Cwin the job,=
=E2=80=9D and avoid =E2=80=9Clos[ing] the market.=E2=80=9D In communication=
s with these Albemarle Subsidiary personnel, Vietnam Agent=E2=80=99s princi=
pal referred to using the commission increase to appease government officia=
ls. His messages regarding the increase included numerous coded references =
to his =E2=80=9CFriend=E2=80=9D (a key decision-maker at Vietnam Refinery 1=
) and the =E2=80=9CFriend=E2=80=99s=E2=80=9D views on the desired level of =
Vietnam Agent=E2=80=99s commission. Without the full details of the nature =
of communications with Vietnam Agent, Refinery Solutions managers at Albema=
rle Netherlands and Albemarle Europe sprl (=E2=80=9CAlbemarle Europe=E2=80=
=9D) approved an increase to Vietnam=C2=A0Agent=E2=80=99s commission, to 6.=
5 percent, in March 2015.</p></blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">And:</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The regional director warned Sales=
 Executive by email that it was =E2=80=9Cclear to [him]=E2=80=9D that India=
 Agent intended to use a portion of its commission to =E2=80=9Chandle=E2=80=
=9D the Senior India Official, as well as officials =E2=80=9Cmany levels be=
low.=E2=80=9D The regional director expressed his concern that engaging Ind=
ia Agent would cause Albemarle to violate the FCPA.=C2=A0</p></blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">And:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In April 2012, an official of Indonesia State-=
Owned Customer urged Albemarle Subsidiary personnel to replace Albemarle=E2=
=80=99s existing agent with Indonesia Agent. The official reported that a k=
ey decision-maker at the customer (=E2=80=9CIndonesia Official=E2=80=9D) wa=
s =E2=80=9Cvery close friend[s]=E2=80=9D with Indonesia Agent=E2=80=99s pre=
sident and that Indonesia Official=E2=80=99s son served on Indonesia Agent=
=E2=80=99s board of directors. Albemarle Subsidiary managers in Asia and Eu=
rope understood that, if they refused to use Indonesia Agent, Albemarle wou=
ld =E2=80=9Close the business opportunity=E2=80=9D to sell catalysts to Ind=
onesia State-Owned Customer. =E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">During a February 2013 meeting in Singapore wi=
th three sales personnel of Albemarle Subsidiaries in the Asia Pacific regi=
on, Indonesia Agent requested a commission increase expressly to fund bribe=
s to Indonesia State-Owned Customer officials, purportedly to compete with =
one of Albemarle=E2=80=99s competitors.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I guess if I was a local agent for a multinati=
onal company I would go to these meetings and say =E2=80=9Cyou need to doub=
le=C2=A0my commission rate to compensate me for my time, effort and experti=
se,=E2=80=9D but then I=E2=80=99d do a really exaggerated wink.</p>
