<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">At the University of Tampa, Anthony Viggiano a=
nd three classmates faced off against another school in the 2018 =E2=80=9CE=
thics Invitational.=E2=80=9D Hosted by the CFA Institute=E2=80=99s local br=
anch, the competition tested which team could best tackle dilemmas they=E2=
=80=99d face as financial professionals.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Viggiano=E2=80=99s team won and walked off wit=
h a $1,000 prize.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">A few years later, on Wall Street, first at Bl=
ackstone Inc. and then at Goldman Sachs Group Inc., Viggiano failed multipl=
e ethical challenges, according to federal prosecutors, who charged him wit=
h being at the center of an insider trading scheme. =E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">After the DOJ unsealed the indictment, Maxwell=
 Grimard, president of the CFA Society Tampa Bay, said the ethics competiti=
on was =E2=80=9Cgenerally a well received and productive event.=E2=80=9D</p=
>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But he acknowledged that it=E2=80=99s =E2=80=
=9Can unfortunate thing that a past participant now is involved in somethin=
g that is counter to what they learned about.=E2=80=9D</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CIt is ironic that past performance is=
 no indication of future results,=E2=80=9D he said.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">We <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusin=
ess.com/click/32912729.260424/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL=
