f hiding his insider trading. He kind of had a gut sense of how insider tra=
ding law and enforcement worked, which is important if you are doing inside=
r trading.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I just feel like if you spend too much time ma=
stering the nuances of ethics then you are probably becoming less ethical? =
The nuances are the least ethical parts of ethics.=C2=A0If you find yoursel=
f saying =E2=80=9Cactually subparagraph (j) of Section 173 of the rules qua=
lifies the rule in Section 124,=E2=80=9D or whatever, are you arguing to do=
 something=C2=A0<em>more=C2=A0</em>ethical, or=C2=A0<em>less=C2=A0</em>ethi=
cal?=C2=A0</p>
